cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.AR, cs.NA, cs.SE

Reasoning: 

- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses parallelization techniques for stencil codes in both shared and distributed memory environments. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses optimization techniques for improving the performance of stencil codes. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of shared caches in multicore environments. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of temporal blocking to improve the performance of stencil codes. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of new algorithms and optimization techniques for balancing the trend towards bandwidth-starved multicore chips.
